OL,3,CCompany fined #200k after 71-year-
OL,4,Cold's death from harmful gas exposure
OL,6,FA factory producing cellulose film
OL,7,Fpackaging has been fined #200,000,
OL,8,Ffollowing a worker's death from
OL,9,Fexposure to a harmful gas.
OL,11,FAlexander Cole, 71, who worked at
OL,12,FFutamura Chemical UK in Wigton, was
OL,13,Ffound collapsed in a pump room on
OL,14,FDecember 24 2021, having been exposed
OL,15,Fto hydrogen sulphide gas - a clear gas
OL,16,Fwith a 'rotten egg' smell.
